Frame & MAC Address

Chapt 2

NIC: Network Interface Card
 - Integrated into every computer
 - Connects to hub

HUB: Act as interface to allow alot of computer to interconnect to share resources (Ex: LAN server)


GOAL
 - How are data move from one computer to another in a local area network?


Data is not sent through long continuous stream but sent through discrete chunks 

Frame and Packet are similar but different

Frame ex: 01001000100. 
Packetized data: Chunk of frame

Frame are generated in NIC. 
 - Data is generated in application. 
 - Data is then sent into network card
 - NC creates the frame and sent into network
 - Alternately NIC takes frame, data is pulled, and sent into a software. Frame is deleted in NIC.
 - Physical and Data Link occur in NIC. 

MAC address uses hexadecimal and use values of 0-9 and A-F

